<Layout title="About" description="Learn about the POACRE Trails Committee and the history of our community trail system in Chesapeake Ranch Estates.">
  <section style="padding-top: var(--spacing-xl);">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About CRE Trails</h1>
      
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);">
        <div>
          <h2>Our Mission</h2>
          <p>The POACRE Trails Committee is dedicated to maintaining and improving the trail system within Chesapeake Ranch Estates for the enjoyment and benefit of our community members and their guests.</p>
          
          <p>We believe that access to natural spaces and outdoor recreation is essential to quality of life. Our trails provide opportunities for exercise, relaxation, wildlife observation, and connecting with nature without leaving the neighborhood.</p>

          <h2>What We Do</h2>
          <p>The trails committee works year-round to ensure our trail system remains safe, accessible, and enjoyable for all users. Our activities include:</p>
          
          <ul style="margin-left: var(--spacing-lg); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);">
            <li>Regular trail maintenance and clearing</li>
            <li>Installing and maintaining trail markers and signage</li>
            <li>Planning trail improvements and expansions</li>
            <li>Organizing volunteer work days</li>
            <li>Monitoring trail conditions and safety</li>
            <li>Coordinating with the Property Owners Association</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>POACRE Trails Committee</h3>
            <p>The Property Owners Association of Chesapeake Ranch Estates (POACRE) Trails Committee is composed of volunteer residents who share a passion for outdoor recreation and community service.</p>
            
            <p>The committee meets several times per year to plan maintenance activities, discuss improvements, and coordinate volunteer efforts. All residents are welcome to attend meetings and participate in trail maintenance days.</p>

            <div class="info-box" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-md);">
              <h4>üìÖ Committee Meetings</h4>
              <p>Meetings are held several times per year. Check our Facebook page or contact us for the next scheduled meeting.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-md);">
              <h4>ü§ù Join Us</h4>
              <p>Interested in joining the committee or volunteering? We'd love to have you! <a href="/volunteer">Learn more about getting involved</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <h2>Trail System Overview</h2>
        <p>Our trail network consists of multiple interconnected loops that wind through the wooded areas of Chesapeake Ranch Estates. The trails are marked with color-coded markers to help users navigate the system.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-3" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>üå≤ Natural Beauty</h3>
            <p>Experience the diverse flora and fauna of Southern Maryland's forests. Our trails showcase the natural beauty of the region throughout all four seasons.</p>
          </div>

